#modeling #magazinefeature #fashionphotography

03.25.23 💍

My sister had told me her work had a benefits program where she could take a +1 to one of a couple landmarks in San Francisco. She sent me a screenshot of the benefits website (which I later found out was a fake website she created on Figma) and said she hadn’t been to Coit Tower before and wanted to check it out and dress nice for it. 

When we got to the top, she opened the door and I see Prasham standing there on the private balcony. I had so many emotions all at once and I couldn’t believe it was happening. We walked over to see the view before he made the sweetest speech and got down on one knee. It was absolutely the most beautiful proposal I could have ever imagined, far beyond anything I could have ever dreamt of. I can not describe how lucky I am to call the most thoughtful, caring, loving person I know my best friend and now, my fiancé ♥️

This was the first of many surprises that day and the lengths our family and friends went to make this the most memorable and special day of my entire life, I am beyond grateful for. Cheers to a new chapter🥂

📸: @ianchinphotography 
#proposal #engagement

Part II: Engagement Brunch🥂

I had so many feels putting this together 🥰 After the proposal, we decided to get brunch with our siblings. Little did I know, they had actually planned to surprise me with our family and friends. So many of them had flown in from all across the country and every single one of them had woken up early to help decorate and set up the place! I can’t even begin to quantify how lucky I am to have such amazing, genuine, loving friends and family 🤍

#engagement #proposal
